---++ Making Allocations


These steps are needed.

---+++ Storage Area Registration

Each OSG Storage Element participating in opportunistic storage is registered by the OSG production coordinator in the allocation database. 

   1. The PC runs an OSG Discovery Tool [[FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_discovery_utility][storage area discovery utility]] of the PC Utilities to discover storage areas which qualify as public storage. 
   1. Upon verification, the PC runs a [[FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_registration_utilit][storage area registration utility]] which saves the output of the tool into the Storage Area Registry of the Allocation Accounting Service for every VO that has installed the AAS and requested storage. 
   1. The PC runs the [[FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_registry_broadcast][storage area registry broadcast tool]] to propagate that information to all other AAS instances. 
   1. The PC runs the [[FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_registration_test_u][storage area registration test utility]], which verifies that the above information has been successfully entered in the databases.

---+++ Public Storage Monitoring

The step is needed to support public storage allocation. These actions could be performed by a VOA-owned cron job

   1. The Pigeon Tool [[http://home.fnal.gov/~dstrain/pigeon][storage area verification tool]] of the VOA Utilities is invoked by the VOA.
   1. The verification tool updates the VO’s Access Record Repository Catalog (ARR) with the discovery and access results using the [[FSSCommandReference#Storage_resource_update_utility][storage resource update utility]]. 

---+++ Requesting an Allocation

   1. To request an allocation, the VOA communicates with the PC, and includes the following information.
   * The size of the allocation
   * The needed lifetime of the allocation. The expiration time of the allocation will be set using this lifetime and the time that the allocation is made.
   * Optionally, other requirements pertaining to the site’s storage and compute resources.

The VOA may use the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_request_tool][allocation request tool]] to assist in composing the request.


---+++ Granting Allocations

When a VO requests space, an allocation must be done on a registered storage area.

   1. The PC runs the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_decision_tool][allocation decision tool]] that shows the PC the storage areas that could meet the allocation request.
   1. The PC selects a storage resource which meets the needs of the allocation.
   1. The PC enters the allocation into the AAS of every VO using the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_update_utility][allocation update utility]]. This redundancy serves as a backup in case the VO loses its AAS database. 
   1. The PC checks that the allocation has been successfully entered by running the [[FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_info_utility][storage area info utility]].
   1. The VOA confirms the allocation by running the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_test_utility][allocation test utility]].

