---++ Changing an Allocation

   1. The VOA communicates to the PC a request to release, resize, or change the lifetime of an allocation. The VOA may use the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_request_tool][allocation request tool]] to assist in composing the request. If the request is to release an allocation, it should first be cleaned up (see below).
   1. The PC uses the [[FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_info_utility][storage area info utility]] to decide whether the request can be met.
   1. The PC uses the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_update_utility][allocation update utility]] to change the corresponding attribute on the allocation object in the AAS of every VO.


---++ Allocation or Dataset Cleanup by a VO

Allocations are normally kept clean by users defining collections of files called &quot;datasets&quot;, and deleting datasets when they expire or are no longer needed. See

   1. The VOA or user calls the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_cleanup_tool][allocation cleanup tool]] or the [[FSSCommandReference#Dataset_cleanup_tool][dataset cleanup tool]]. The allocation  cleanup tool does the following.
   * The tool checks the expiration attribute of every allocation object
   * For every expired allocation, it finds all datasets that refer to the allocation. This includes the default dataset for files that are not in any other dataset.
   * It deletes each dataset using the dataset operation tool.


---++ Allocation or Dataset Cleanup using the Operations Toolkit

If a VO does not clean up.

   1. The PC checks for expired allocations using the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_query_utility][allocation query utility]]. 
   1. The PC may work with the VOA of an expired allocation to extend the lifetime of the allocation, or to have the VO remove its files.

Otherwise, the following steps are done

   1. The PC runs a tool to construct a list of site file names of all the files in the expired allocation.
   1. The PC forwards the list of site file names to the site administrator.
   1. The site administrator examines the list to try to ensure that no harm will be done by the deletions.
   1. The site administrator executes the [[FSSCommandReference#Public_storage_cleanup_tool][public storage cleanup tool]] using the list as input.
   1. The site administrator informs the PC that the files have been deleted.
   1. The PC uses the [[FSSCommandReference#Allocation_update_utility][allocation update utility]] to set the space used attribute of the allocation object to zero in all AAS instances.

